{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Replace the terms 'disability' and 'disabled' with 'people of determination'",
        "additional_details": "We believe the term \u2018people of determination\u2019 empowers and acknowledges the tenacity to progress.\r\n \r\nThe terminology \u2018disability\u2019 is seen by some as implying it is something caused by the individual, rather than society\u2019s unwillingness to meet the needs of \u2018people of determination\u2019.\r\n \r\nRephrasing from \u2018disabled\u2019 and \u2018disability\u2019 to \u2018people of determination\u2019 in Government documents and legislation, could help provide an empowering mindset and lead to a barrier-free society. By avoiding limiting labels, the need for terminology pertaining to \u2018disability\u2019 could end and help improve equality.\r\n \r\nThe UAE is taking a similar approach: https://u.ae/en/information-and-services/social-affairs/people-of-determination\r\n",
        "background": "We want the Government to stop using the limiting terms \u2018disabled\u2019 and \u2018disability\u2019, which for some reflect negative victim-based identity such as an inability to progress or achieve.",
